496
00:42:53,170 --> 00:42:54,790
Who was this guy?

497
00:42:56,650 --> 00:42:58,000
"What happened?"

498
00:42:58,000 --> 00:43:00,960
"What was so bad
that made you sob like that?"

499
00:43:03,560 --> 00:43:07,230
"When you said it was
because Chang Gook Young died"

500
00:43:07,230 --> 00:43:10,690
"I suddenly hated Chang Gook Young
who made you cry."

501
00:43:10,690 --> 00:43:13,520
"I was jealous of him
and wanted to be him."

502
00:43:13,520 --> 00:43:15,690
Tell him that Do Kyung
wants to meet him.

503
00:43:16,650 --> 00:43:19,250
"When I got home,
I ripped up all his pictures."

504
00:43:19,250 --> 00:43:20,850
"I was furious."

505
00:43:20,850 --> 00:43:22,670
Isn't he cute?

506
00:43:22,670 --> 00:43:25,020
Come on, he's so cute.

507
00:43:28,690 --> 00:43:29,880
What is it?

508
00:43:29,880 --> 00:43:32,730
It's a love letter
sent to you in high school.

509
00:43:47,170 --> 00:43:51,500
<i>I knew right away that
this letter was meant for you.</i>

510
00:43:51,500 --> 00:43:53,830
<i>I didn't want to give it to you.</i>

511
00:43:54,750 --> 00:43:56,940
<i>I didn't want to give it to you.</i>

512
00:44:03,750 --> 00:44:07,190
<i>It's okay. Grades aren't everything.</i>

513
00:44:12,610 --> 00:44:16,860
<i>You grew up being loved by your parents. </i>

514
00:44:17,170 --> 00:44:21,020
<i>I didn't want you to
have more love from a boy. </i>

515
00:44:21,020 --> 00:44:23,190
<i>I felt like you were taking
something from me. </i>

516
00:44:24,020 --> 00:44:27,190
<i>I've been throwing away
many letters all these years. </i>

517
00:44:27,190 --> 00:44:29,630
<i>I just couldn't throw away this letter.</i>

518
00:44:30,250 --> 00:44:32,380
<i>Because it wasn't meant for me.</i>

519
00:44:35,080 --> 00:44:40,000
<i>I thought I'd be able to return
this letter to you smiling some day.</i>

520
00:44:40,000 --> 00:44:44,730
<i>When I became good enough
to admit that I was jealous of you</i>

521
00:44:44,730 --> 00:44:48,250
<i>I might be able to
return this letter to you.</i>

522
00:44:48,480 --> 00:44:52,940
<i>That's why I haven't
been able to throw it away. </i>

523
00:44:52,940 --> 00:44:55,150
<i>I'm not good enough yet.</i>

524
00:44:55,150 --> 00:44:57,600
<i>I feel that I need to
return it to you now.</i>

525
00:44:57,600 --> 00:45:01,110
<i>I should return it first
and focus on becoming good. </i>

526
00:45:01,610 --> 00:45:03,480
<i>I am going to try. </i>

527
00:45:03,480 --> 00:45:05,480
<i>I am going to go for it.</i>

528
00:45:06,830 --> 00:45:10,790
<i>It took 13 years for this letter
to find its way back to you.</i>

529
00:45:11,310 --> 00:45:13,000
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

530
00:45:13,560 --> 00:45:16,600
<i>I also feel bad for the boy who wrote it.</i>

531
00:45:18,750 --> 00:45:21,860
<i>I thought I was the one who
kept comparing myself to her. </i>

532
00:45:22,750 --> 00:45:25,900
<i>She says she's kept
comparing herself to me. </i>

533
00:45:25,900 --> 00:45:29,560
<i>Am I happy now that I know
how she's felt all along?</i>

534
00:45:29,560 --> 00:45:31,920
<i>Is it comforting?</i>

535
00:45:31,920 --> 00:45:34,500
<i>Why do I feel sad?</i>

536
00:45:38,080 --> 00:45:40,770
Bitch! Have a good life!

537
00:45:40,770 --> 00:45:45,250
<i>Perhaps the boy who threw
a rock at our window back then...</i>

538
00:45:45,250 --> 00:45:46,510
Hey!

539
00:45:47,400 --> 00:45:50,460
<i>I wonder if he had
feelings for me for real.</i>

540
00:45:55,020 --> 00:45:58,380
Yes. Lee Kang Yong?

541
00:45:58,380 --> 00:46:00,250
<i>Correct. Lee Kang Yong. </i>

542
00:46:00,250 --> 00:46:02,900
<i>He might have been
in the class of seven or eight.</i>

543
00:46:05,080 --> 00:46:07,630
- Here he is.
- Can you take a photo and send it?

544
00:46:07,630 --> 00:46:09,440
Okay.

545
00:46:17,170 --> 00:46:19,080
- Let me see.
- No, no need to see it.

546
00:46:19,080 --> 00:46:21,000
- Let me see who the punk is.
- No need to see.

547
00:46:21,000 --> 00:46:22,460
- Give it.
- What are you going to do?

548
00:46:22,460 --> 00:46:24,650
No, no, no.

549
00:46:24,650 --> 00:46:27,210
- Let me see.
- Don't do it. No need to see.

550
00:46:27,210 --> 00:46:30,060
Hold on! Wait!

551
00:46:30,060 --> 00:46:31,190
What's up?

552
00:46:31,880 --> 00:46:33,270
<i>Where are you?</i>

553
00:46:33,270 --> 00:46:34,670
I'm at Hee Ran's.

554
00:46:34,670 --> 00:46:37,110
I will stay over at her place tonight.

555
00:46:38,100 --> 00:46:39,750
I'm serious that I'm at Hee Ran's.

556
00:46:39,750 --> 00:46:41,560
Put her on the phone then.

557
00:46:42,900 --> 00:46:45,210
Put Hee Ran on the phone.

558
00:46:45,210 --> 00:46:47,000
Darn it.

559
00:46:47,000 --> 00:46:50,880
I'm old enough to stay out.

560
00:46:50,880 --> 00:46:53,420
Why are you acting this way?
You told him to take me.

561
00:46:53,420 --> 00:46:55,630
Do you want me to come over right now?

562
00:46:55,630 --> 00:46:57,940
Come home before you get dragged back.

563
00:47:18,130 --> 00:47:21,250
You think it's good
as long as I come home at night, huh?

564
00:47:21,250 --> 00:47:23,540
I can't do whatever just because
I have to come home early?

565
00:47:23,540 --> 00:47:25,540
I can do whatever during the day too.

566
00:47:26,250 --> 00:47:28,980
Can't you keep
your love life more private?

567
00:47:28,980 --> 00:47:32,150
Why did you let
everybody know it all, huh?

568
00:47:32,150 --> 00:47:34,170
You have no pride, girl.

569
00:47:34,170 --> 00:47:37,580
If I ever catch you cooking for him
and going in and out of his place

570
00:47:37,580 --> 00:47:40,600
- I will kill you.
- He cooked for me tonight.

571
00:47:40,600 --> 00:47:42,460
Why did he have to cook for you?

572
00:47:42,460 --> 00:47:44,880
Why would he cook for you
when you two are going to break up soon?

573
00:47:44,880 --> 00:47:46,100
We have no food in our house?

574
00:47:46,100 --> 00:47:49,290
How do you know that
we're going to break up soon?

575
00:47:51,630 --> 00:47:55,310
Excuse me. Don't do this.

576
00:47:55,790 --> 00:47:57,420
Come on.

577
00:48:00,250 --> 00:48:02,880
I told him this.

578
00:48:02,880 --> 00:48:05,080
If he ever wants to marry you

579
00:48:05,080 --> 00:48:08,610
come to Suh Hee's wedding
and if not, don't show up.

580
00:48:08,610 --> 00:48:10,750
That bastard didn't show up!

581
00:48:12,940 --> 00:48:16,610
I'm sure he had his reasons.

582
00:48:17,330 --> 00:48:21,730
Now all our family knows about you.

583
00:48:21,730 --> 00:48:23,440
Not anymore.

584
00:48:23,440 --> 00:48:25,330
Know that.

585
00:48:25,330 --> 00:48:27,900
If you still want to see him,
see him secretly.

586
00:48:59,330 --> 00:49:01,710
Why did you have to say that to him?

587
00:49:01,710 --> 00:49:03,540
Why did you pressure him?

588
00:49:03,540 --> 00:49:05,000
I don't have to get married.

589
00:49:05,000 --> 00:49:07,900
If you weren't going to marry, why bother
planning to bring him to the party?

590
00:49:09,380 --> 00:49:12,480
Because I thought it wouldn't
make you look as bad at the wedding.

591
00:49:12,480 --> 00:49:14,520
I knew that everyone
would be talking about me

592
00:49:14,520 --> 00:49:17,000
so I planned on it so you both
wouldn't feel so ashamed.

593
00:49:17,000 --> 00:49:18,710
If he had come

594
00:49:18,710 --> 00:49:22,310
you wouldn't have had
to feel so ashamed!

595
00:49:40,020 --> 00:49:41,500
Hello?

596
00:49:42,190 --> 00:49:44,210
What's wrong?

597
00:49:44,210 --> 00:49:46,110
I cried.

598
00:49:49,460 --> 00:49:51,130
How come?

599
00:49:51,130 --> 00:49:52,770
My mom hit me.

600
00:49:52,770 --> 00:49:55,290
Because I lied that
I was at Hee Ran's.

601
00:49:55,290 --> 00:49:59,520
I'm too old to get beaten up by her.

602
00:50:04,440 --> 00:50:06,420
Don't cry.

603
00:50:08,000 --> 00:50:10,000
Don't cry.

604
00:50:10,000 --> 00:50:12,540
My mom is giving me
a dirty look now to hang up.

605
00:50:12,540 --> 00:50:14,630
I will call you later.

606
00:50:32,480 --> 00:50:34,960
When I'm about to die

607
00:50:35,690 --> 00:50:38,650
if I think back on this moment

608
00:50:41,060 --> 00:50:43,500
this will mean nothing.

609
00:50:45,020 --> 00:50:47,460
This means nothing.

610
00:50:49,480 --> 00:50:52,290
Let's go for it.

611
00:51:21,310 --> 00:51:23,580
Soo Kyung, are you okay?

612
00:51:24,560 --> 00:51:27,190
That's enough. Stop now.

613
00:51:29,540 --> 00:51:31,650
Soo Kyung.

614
00:51:32,100 --> 00:51:33,730
I'm sorry.

615
00:51:34,330 --> 00:51:37,880
I've kissed so many women before.

616
00:51:38,610 --> 00:51:42,060
- Honestly, with you...
- I understand.

617
00:51:42,670 --> 00:51:43,880
Go.

618
00:51:45,560 --> 00:51:47,670
Good try.

619
00:51:48,310 --> 00:51:52,000
How can I possibly get out of your life
when you're carrying my child?

620
00:52:36,230 --> 00:52:38,650
See what happens if you dance!

621
00:53:47,540 --> 00:53:50,330
- Can I have one pitcher of beer here?
- Sure.

622
00:53:51,000 --> 00:53:52,750
Gosh.

623
00:53:52,750 --> 00:53:55,130
I had no idea about this chicken place.

624
00:53:55,130 --> 00:53:57,190
Why beer and chicken during the day?

625
00:53:57,190 --> 00:53:59,610
You seemed so happy that
you were on top of the world.

626
00:53:59,610 --> 00:54:01,480
Now what happened?

627
00:54:03,210 --> 00:54:06,730
Why do I always lower myself
when I'm in a relationship?

628
00:54:06,730 --> 00:54:10,040
I was going to go for it
until I get rejected completely.

629
00:54:10,080 --> 00:54:14,000
I didn't care if I loved him
more than he did.

630
00:54:14,710 --> 00:54:17,900
- Now I feel differently.
- Are you still talking about that?

631
00:54:18,920 --> 00:54:20,690
Honestly...

632
00:54:20,690 --> 00:54:24,440
I don't understand why you think
Park Do Kyung will marry you.

633
00:54:24,440 --> 00:54:29,290
Don't you have to take time
and see if he's the right one for you?

634
00:54:29,290 --> 00:54:32,460
Love comes at once
when it happens.

635
00:54:32,460 --> 00:54:35,230
It doesn't let me take
my time and think about it.

636
00:54:35,230 --> 00:54:38,210
I want to hold his hands,
sleep with him, and marry him.

637
00:54:38,210 --> 00:54:40,830
For me, it doesn't
always go in that order.

638
00:54:40,830 --> 00:54:42,190
When I fall in love

639
00:54:42,190 --> 00:54:45,210
in my head, I'm already sleeping
with him and being married to him.

640
00:54:45,210 --> 00:54:46,980
- Is it just me?
- Yes.

641
00:54:46,980 --> 00:54:50,290
- It's just you who thinks that way.
- I see.

642
00:54:55,170 --> 00:54:57,830
<i>[The Man Next Door]</i>

643
00:55:00,790 --> 00:55:03,630
- Why aren't you answering?
- I want to play hard to get.

644
00:55:06,400 --> 00:55:09,460
<i>Your call is being redirected...</i>

645
00:55:15,690 --> 00:55:18,130
<i>[Provisional Seizure Notice]</i>

646
00:55:21,830 --> 00:55:24,980
<i>[Decision]</i>

647
00:55:28,610 --> 00:55:30,710
By any chance...

648
00:55:35,690 --> 00:55:37,190
Don't worry about this.

649
00:55:37,190 --> 00:55:38,830
Is it a private loan?

650
00:55:38,830 --> 00:55:41,900
He and I have
made deals many times before.

651
00:55:41,900 --> 00:55:44,480
He's just doing this for no reason.

652
00:55:44,480 --> 00:55:48,310
He's never said anything
when I was late with my payment.

653
00:55:48,310 --> 00:55:50,060
He will lift the seizure notice soon.

654
00:55:50,060 --> 00:55:51,100
Don't worry about it.

655
00:55:51,100 --> 00:55:53,940
Don't think about getting
money elsewhere to stop that.

656
00:55:53,940 --> 00:55:55,670
Just leave it.

657
00:55:56,480 --> 00:56:00,290
Don't worry. I will handle it, okay?

658
00:56:00,670 --> 00:56:02,940
I'm saying don't worry. Just leave it.

659
00:57:00,060 --> 00:57:04,110
When I was little,
I'd kick a can on my way home.

660
00:57:04,110 --> 00:57:07,580
I got so attached to that can
that I couldn't leave it outside.

661
00:57:09,790 --> 00:57:11,710
I'm a can.

662
00:57:11,710 --> 00:57:14,880
I told myself "I'm a mere can"
and went inside.

663
00:57:14,880 --> 00:57:18,790
But I came out and took it inside.

664
00:57:19,150 --> 00:57:21,130
That's cute.

665
00:57:21,710 --> 00:57:23,650
Why didn't you answer my calls?

666
00:57:25,000 --> 00:57:27,270
- Because I'm mad.
- Why?

667
00:57:33,900 --> 00:57:35,830
I thought we both liked each other.

668
00:57:35,830 --> 00:57:37,400
But it seems that I'm the only
one who feels that way.

669
00:57:37,400 --> 00:57:39,940
If you like me
89 on the scale, not 100

670
00:57:39,940 --> 00:57:42,360
then tell me so.
I will like you for the same amount.

671
00:57:42,360 --> 00:57:44,250
I feel it's only 89 on the scale
when I thought it was 100.

672
00:57:44,250 --> 00:57:46,170
Every time that happens...

673
00:57:47,210 --> 00:57:49,310
I don't feel good.

674
00:57:49,310 --> 00:57:51,230
So tell me so I can match that level.

675
00:57:51,230 --> 00:57:52,920
It's 100 on the scale.

676
00:57:52,920 --> 00:57:57,400
The 100 you're referring to
and mine seem different.

677
00:57:58,190 --> 00:58:00,270
Mine is seriously 100 on the scale.

678
00:58:02,250 --> 00:58:05,190
Because you're mad, you're
starting to call me "mister," huh?

679
00:58:06,920 --> 00:58:09,520
- Go.
- Let's say bye after I give you a hug.

680
00:58:10,290 --> 00:58:12,730
If I leave without one,
I'll be down.

681
00:58:13,830 --> 00:58:15,880
I may get angry too.

682
00:58:27,630 --> 00:58:29,190
Go now.

683
00:59:04,420 --> 00:59:06,400
I will let you take away everything.

684
00:59:06,400 --> 00:59:08,440
I will go down completely.

685
00:59:09,420 --> 00:59:11,060
I will give you my arm if you ask.

686
00:59:11,060 --> 00:59:13,440
I will give you my leg if you ask.

687
00:59:19,400 --> 00:59:21,270
Just let me live.

688
00:59:21,690 --> 00:59:25,540
Come inside. You will get
recorded by the CCTV there.

689
00:59:52,210 --> 00:59:54,670
One sunny day...

690
00:59:55,690 --> 01:00:00,730
I am walking in my favorite suit.

691
01:00:01,460 --> 01:00:06,790
This guy suddenly kicks my knee.

692
01:00:09,770 --> 01:00:13,400
So I ask him why.

693
01:00:13,400 --> 01:00:15,790
Do you know what that punk tells me?

694
01:00:17,020 --> 01:00:18,500
He says it was a mistake.

695
01:00:18,500 --> 01:00:21,080
After he put me through so much

696
01:00:21,080 --> 01:00:22,790
he says it was a mistake.

697
01:00:24,230 --> 01:00:26,690
But that's not the end of the story.

698
01:00:26,690 --> 01:00:31,170
It turns out that now
he's wearing my favorite suit.

699
01:00:32,330 --> 01:00:35,560
He kicks my knee by accident.

700
01:00:35,560 --> 01:00:37,690
And he steals my suit too.

701
01:00:38,520 --> 01:00:43,020
What would you do
if you were me?

702
01:00:44,920 --> 01:00:47,040
Spare my life.

703
01:01:19,760 --> 01:01:20,760
<i>[The Man Next Door]</i>

704
01:01:27,810 --> 01:01:29,690
I'm sorry.

705
01:01:32,790 --> 01:01:34,880
I can't sleep.

706
01:01:36,860 --> 01:01:38,770
I'm angry.

707
01:01:39,380 --> 01:01:41,380
I miss you.

708
01:01:43,710 --> 01:01:45,400
<i>Come over.</i>

709
01:01:47,380 --> 01:01:51,270
Come over even if
you're 89 on the scale.

710
01:01:52,080 --> 01:01:53,880
Come over.

711
01:01:55,020 --> 01:01:57,190
I can't come.

712
01:02:00,190 --> 01:02:02,560
Were you 70 on the scale?

713
01:02:08,250 --> 01:02:10,500
<i>Right before I was dying...</i>

714
01:02:10,500 --> 01:02:14,690
<i>I was regretting that I didn't
love her with all my heart. </i>

715
01:02:14,690 --> 01:02:17,150
<i>That's why I made another decision.</i>

716
01:02:17,150 --> 01:02:19,250
<i>So here I am.</i>

717
01:02:19,790 --> 01:02:23,400
<i>If I die this time</i>

718
01:02:23,420 --> 01:02:25,960
<i>I will probably regret this moment.</i>

719
01:02:26,690 --> 01:02:28,880
<i>When I'm not being honest.</i>

720
01:02:29,500 --> 01:02:31,630
<i>When I couldn't be honest. </i>

721
01:02:32,330 --> 01:02:34,710
<i>When I made her misunderstand.</i>

722
01:02:34,710 --> 01:02:37,380
<i>When I hurt her feelings.</i>

723
01:02:37,790 --> 01:02:43,690
<i>The same way Han Tae Jin couldn't
be honest and hurt her feelings...</i>

724
01:02:43,690 --> 01:02:49,130
<i>Am I making the same mistake right now?</i>

725
01:02:49,940 --> 01:02:54,210
<i>Should I tell her the truth right now?</i>

726
01:02:55,400 --> 01:02:58,170
<i>I might die soon.</i>

727
01:03:03,900 --> 01:03:06,560
<i>If I tell her the truth</i>

728
01:03:06,560 --> 01:03:10,150
<i>would we still be
as happy as we are now?</i>

729
01:03:11,190 --> 01:03:14,500
<i>If she knows that I may die soon</i>

730
01:03:14,500 --> 01:03:20,730
<i>will she still be able
to smile at me like now?</i>

731
01:03:34,600 --> 01:03:36,100
Who did this to you?

732
01:03:36,710 --> 01:03:39,110
Who did this to you?

733
01:03:46,690 --> 01:03:49,420
Didn't you expect that
I'd get beaten up this much?

734
01:03:50,710 --> 01:03:52,900
I expected this.

735
01:04:04,400 --> 01:04:06,730
Compared to what I did to him...

736
01:04:07,790 --> 01:04:09,290
I have to endure everything

737
01:04:09,290 --> 01:04:11,270
including my business failure
and getting beaten up.

738
01:04:13,520 --> 01:04:15,520
It's okay.

739
01:04:17,060 --> 01:04:21,210
Don't you dare go see him.

740
01:04:27,440 --> 01:04:30,020
I'm sorry that I didn't
come to the wedding.

741
01:04:34,290 --> 01:04:36,330
I had my reasons.

742
01:04:38,170 --> 01:04:40,770
Until I die

743
01:04:40,770 --> 01:04:43,150
I won't leave you.

744
01:04:44,900 --> 01:04:48,860
